</dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Amazon Prime Day]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Amazon Prime Day]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Google's NotebookLM personalizes the chatbot experience]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>在<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-io-2023-everything-announced-at-the-event-193758196.html">5 月份的 Google I/O 大会</a>上，该公司透露了其计划全力投入 AI 领域，其中包括<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-unveils-its-multilingual-code-generating-palm-2-language-model-180805304.html">PaLM 2</a> 、 <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-bard-transitions-to-palm-2-and-expands-to-180-countries-172908926.html">Bard</a>及其众多产品的一整套<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-photos-will-use-generative-ai-to-straight-up-change-your-images-171014939.html">智能增强功能</a>。在消费主义的行列中，我们对<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/googles-project-tailwind-is-an-ai-infused-personal-notebook-182728079.html">谷歌的 Project Tailwind</a>进行了简短的讨论，这是一款面向学生的实验产品，作为“人工智能优先的笔记本”来帮助他们保持井井有条。周三，Tailwind 项目完成开发，成为<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://blog.google/technology/ai/notebooklm-google-ai/">NotebookLM</a> (NLM)。</p><p> NLM 本质上是一种附有大型语言模型的笔记软件，它“与您现有的内容相结合，以更快地获得关键见解”。基本上，它是一个不断根据您的特定数据集进行调整的聊天机器人，因此当您向它提出问题时，它只会从该信息中提取信息，而不是从构建底层模型的集体知识中提取信息。这种“源头扎根”的过程可确保虚拟助手紧扣主题并提供更相关的响应。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>该虚拟助手可以完成所有正常的聊天机器人任务，包括总结新添加的文档、深入回答有关文本语料库的问题以及从该信息生成新内容。 NLM 将立即提供给美国的一小群 Beta 测试人员，以便为进一步的开发提供反馈，不过目前还没有关于何时向公众提供的消息。如果您想尽早亲自尝试，请在<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://notebooklm.google.com/signup">候补名单</a>上注册。</p><p></p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/googles-notebooklm-personalizes-the-chatbot-experience-164135240.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/googles-notebooklm-personalizes-the-chatbot-experience-164135240.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 6f730723-0a8a-43a2-b5be-176fd8ec5fb8</guid><dc:creator>安德鲁·塔兰托拉</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 12 Jul 2023 16:41:35 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689180096</ingested><modified> 2023-07-12T16:41:42+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Small Businesses]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Andrew Tarantola]]></category><media:content height="4024" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/2c29c520-20d2-11ee-afcd-2138b67b0c1e" width="6048"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="4024" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/2c29c520-20d2-11ee-afcd-2138b67b0c1e" width="6048"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[primeimages via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[StockRobot with high frequency trading robot trade in cryptocurrencies stockmarket]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[StockRobot with high frequency trading robot trade in cryptocurrencies stockmarket]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[James Webb telescope marks first anniversary with an image of a nearby stellar nursery]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>很难相信，詹姆斯·韦伯太空望远镜在一整年前就开始发出<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/james-webb-space-telescope-first-image-223020435.html"><ins>令人惊叹的宇宙图像</ins></a>。为了纪念这一里程碑，美国宇航局让望远镜发挥其最擅长的能力，向我们展示酷炫的太空照片。最新和最伟大的图像描绘了一个（相对）附近的太空区域<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.nasa.gov/feature/goddard/2023/webb-celebrates-first-year-of-science-with-new-image"><ins>，它是某种银河托儿所，</ins></a>有 50 颗年轻的恒星，有一天可能会形成类似于我们自己的系统。</p><p>蛇夫座 Rho 云复合体距地球约 390 光年，与浩瀚的太空相比，这只是微不足道的，但使用现有技术仍需要 14,500,000 年的旅行才能到达那里。图像中显示的恒星的质量大多与我们心爱的太阳相似，有些甚至拥有星周盘的起点，这些星周盘是行星诞生的气体和尘埃的漩涡环。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/caff39e0-20ce-11ee-beed-6c4dbd8844a5" style="height:1873px;width:2000px;" alt="图片来自詹姆斯·韦伯太空望远镜" data-uuid="cae8adfb-f1a2-33f1-aeed-c24b68d9edf2"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">美国宇航局</div></figure><p>那么那些华丽的红色漩涡是什么？这些是巨大的氢分子射流，当一颗恒星冲破其诞生时的宇宙尘埃包层并暂时延伸到宇宙中时，就会发生这种情况。新的生命是美丽的，是红色的。多为红色。</p><p> “韦伯拍摄的蛇夫座 Rho 图像让我们能够以新的清晰度见证恒星生命周期中非常短暂的时期。我们自己的太阳很久以前就经历过这样的阶段，现在我们有了技术来看到另一颗恒星故事的开始，”项目科学家克劳斯·蓬托皮丹(Klaus Pontoppidan)说。</p><p>在过去的一年里，詹姆斯·韦伯太空望远镜遭受了一次又一次的打击。其中有第一张<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/jwst-captures-images-of-the-first-asteroid-belts-seen-beyond-the-solar-system-192847989.html"><ins>星际小行星带的图像、</ins></a>描绘<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/jwst-captures-images-of-the-first-asteroid-belts-seen-beyond-the-solar-system-192847989.html"><ins>创世之柱的悲惨场景、</ins></a> <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/james-webb-space-telescope-galaxy-cluster-early-universe-165352781.html"><ins>早期宇宙星系团</ins></a>的图片等等。但至今仍未发现外星人。<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fermi_paradox"><ins>那是怎么回事？</ins></a></p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/james-webb-telescope-marks-first-anniversary-with-an-image-of-a-nearby-stellar-nursery-163444912.html?src =rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/james-webb-telescope-marks-first-anniversary-with-an-image-of-a-nearby-stellar-nursery-163444912.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> e01ed7d8-b65b-4bdd-bda7-3fbcb57634b5</guid><dc:creator>劳伦斯·邦克</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 12 Jul 2023 16:34:44 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689179684</ingested><modified> 2023-07-12T16:34:51+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Science]]></category><category><![CDATA[Space & Astronomy]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Lawrence Bonk]]></category><media:content height="1229" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/a4317300-20ce-11ee-bd9d-abe92f29481f" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1229" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/a4317300-20ce-11ee-bd9d-abe92f29481f" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[NASA]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[James Webb Space Telescope shows off nearby region of space where stars are being born. It's red.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[James Webb Space Telescope Star Birth]]></media:title></media:content></item></channel></rss>